\begin_layout Paragraph*
How to measure the Accruals?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subparagraph*
From acounting reports 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using only some elements in balance sheet and inome statement, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "sloan1996dostock"

\end_inset

 propose a simple measure of 
\begin_inset Formula $Accruals$
\end_inset

 as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Accruals=(\triangle CA-\triangle Cash)-(\triangle CL-\triangle STD-\triangle TP)-Dep
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
where 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\triangle CA$
\end_inset

 is change in current assets,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\triangle Cash$
\end_inset

 is change in cash and equivalent,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\triangle CL$
\end_inset

 is change in current liabilities,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\triangle STD$
\end_inset

 is change in debt included in current liabilities,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\triangle TP$
\end_inset

 is change in income taxes payable,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $Dep$
\end_inset

 is depreciation.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
According to this definition, 
\begin_inset Formula $Accruals$
\end_inset

 has three components: current assets, current liabilities, and depreciations.
\end_layout

