key "teoh1998earnings"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
First
\series default
, they calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $TotalAccruals$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
AC=Net\, Income-Cash\, flows\, from\, operations
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If CF is not available, they replace it with 
\begin_inset Formula Current\, Accruals

\end_inset

 which is the change in noncash current assets minus the change in operating
 current liabilities:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
CA=\triangle\left[current\, assets-cash\right]-\triangle\left[current\, liabilities-current\, maturity\, of\, longterm\, debt\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To reduce the influences of nonstandard classifications of certain items,
 they calculate the current accruals in details: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $CA=\triangle\left[account\, receivables+inventory+other\, current\, assets\right]-\triangle[account\, payable+tax\, payable+other\, current\, liabilities]$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Second
\series default
, they run the regression for firm 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 in year 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{CA_{j,t}}{TA_{j,t-1}}=\alpha_{0}\left(\frac{1}{TA_{j,t-1}}\right)+\alpha_{1}\left(\frac{\triangle Sales_{j,t}}{TA_{j,t-1}}\right)+\epsilon_{j,t},\,\,\,\, j\in2\, digits\, SIC\, code\, peers
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\triangle Sales$
\end_inset

 is change in sales, 
\begin_inset Formula $TA$
\end_inset

 is total assets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\emph on
normal
\emph default
 or 
\emph on
nondiscretionary current accruals
\emph default
 is: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
NDCA_{i,t}=\hat{\alpha}_{0}\left(\frac{1}{TA_{i,t-1}}\right)+\hat{\alpha}_{1}\left(\frac{\triangle Sales_{i,t}-\triangle TR_{i,t}}{TA_{i,t-1}}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\triangle TR$
\end_inset

 is change in trade receivables.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\emph on
abnormal 
\emph default
or the 
\emph on
discretionary current accruals 
\emph default
is:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
DCA_{i,t}=\frac{CA_{i,t}}{TA_{i,t-1}}-NDCA_{i,t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Third
\series default
, repeat the process for total accruals, run the following regression:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{AC_{j,t}}{TA_{j,t-1}}=\beta_{0}\left(\frac{1}{TA_{j,t-1}}\right)+\beta_{1}\left(\frac{\triangle Sales_{j,t}}{TA_{j,t-1}}\right)+\beta_{2}\left(\frac{PPE_{j,t}}{TA_{j,t-1}}\right)+\epsilon_{j,t}\,\,\,\, j\in2\, digits\, SIC\, code\, peers
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\emph on
nondiscretionary total accruals
\emph default
:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
NDTAC_{i,t}=\hat{\beta}_{0}\left(\frac{1}{TA_{i,t-1}}\right)+\hat{\beta}_{1}\left(\frac{\triangle Sales_{i,t}-\triangle TR_{i,t}}{TA_{i,t-1}}\right)+\hat{\beta}_{2}\left(\frac{PPE_{i,t}}{TA_{i,t-1}}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $PPE$
\end_inset

 is gross property, plant, and equipment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The discretionary total accruals: 
\begin_inset Formula $DTAC_{i,t}=\frac{AC_{i,t}}{TA_{i,t-1}}-NDTAC_{i,t}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Fourth
\series default
, define the long-term accruals as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
NDLA_{i,t}=NDTAC_{i,t}-NDCA_{i,t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
DLA_{i,t}=DTAC_{i,t}-DCA_{i,t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

